{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"98237c52-1b5a-46b2-8c36-e091879116d1","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform, VSTest flags move after `--` and use the new syntax:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|--------|---------------------------|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to the test project):\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild` — enables `dotnet test` integration\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` — `--report-trx`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` — `--coverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` — `--crashdump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` — `--hangdump`\n\nThe `--filter` flag stays before `--` because the MSBuild integration forwards it automatically.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"562f4470-4c38-4915-a3bc-50c2e6ec7f07","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. They want to know what the equivalent command would look like.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command. Microsoft.Testing.Platform uses a different CLI syntax:\n\n- `--filter` → `--filter` (same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura`\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the invocation method differs from VSTest. On .NET 8, you'd typically run the test executable directly or use `dotnet run --project <path>` rather than `dotnet test`. Starting with .NET 9 SDK, `dotnet test` gained support for Microsoft.Testing.Platform through the `--testingplatform` switch, but that's not available in .NET 8.\n\nWhen using Microsoft.Testing.Platform, you can pass platform-specific arguments after `--` in the command line. So you'd structure it as `dotnet test -- --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` or invoke the test executable directly with those flags, depending on your .NET version and setup. Refining the command syntax...\n\nI need to clarify the package dependencies for each feature. Code coverage requires the `Microsoft.Testing.Platform.Extensions.CodeCoverage` package, TRX reporting needs `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`, and the crash/hang dump functionality requires their respective extension packages. With all these in place, the command structure with the proper flags should work correctly.","outputTokens":1465,"requestId":"680A:2CF0DF:72880A:79FFBC:6A044DA8"},"id":"6beee9ff-d08e-40c7-bef7-88e86fe79497","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:09:05.358Z","parentId":"a6240776-ab94-4021-b890-4ab227dda0fd"}
